ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It is a good crash course on statistics for clinical studies. I didn't think it was as applicable for simpler lab data.

Excellent course, highly recommended for students looking to immediately apply statical tests to their data. Not for students looking to have an in-depth understanding of the math behind the statistical tests. Recommend that students have minimal other commitments during the two weeks of this course.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course provided me with a good background in choosing the types of statistical analysis I need for drug trial research, but I don't think I'll be doing much of that for my research. In any case, it helped me to think more about the statistical tests I use for my own data analysis.
